<p><i><b>LOC Kargil</b></i> is a 2003 Indian <a href="/wiki/War_film" title="War film">war film</a> based on the <a href="/wiki/Kargil_War" title="Kargil War">Kargil War</a> fought between India and Pakistan, produced and directed by <a href="/wiki/J._P._Dutta" title="J. P. Dutta">J. P. Dutta</a> on J.P. Films banner. Starring a large number of <a href="/wiki/Bollywood" title="Bollywood">Bollywood</a> stars and music composed by <a href="/wiki/Anu_Malik" title="Anu Malik">Anu Malik</a>. The film recorded as <i>Average</i> at box-office.</p>
<p>Upon release <i>LOC</i> received a mixed response critically and commercially. With a running time of 255 minutes, it is one of the longest Indian films ever made and fifth in terms of running time.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> The film is based on the 1999, <a href="/wiki/Operation_Vijay_(1999)" title="Operation Vijay (1999)" class="mw-redirect">Operation Vijay</a> and <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Tololing" title="Battle of Tololing">Battle of Tololing</a> around the <a href="/wiki/Line_of_control" title="Line of control" class="mw-redirect">Line of control</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
